# 🍽️ Yummy - Restaurant Website (Responsive Frontend Interface)

## 📌 Project Overview
**Yummy** is a fully responsive restaurant website built as **Project 1** of the Full Stack Development Internship at **DecodeLabs**. This project focuses on building a clean, user-friendly, and mobile-first frontend interface using **HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript** — without relying on any frontend frameworks.

The goal was to master the fundamentals of responsive web design: semantic structure, flexible layouts, and interactive UI components that work seamlessly across all screen sizes.

---

## 🎯 Objective
Create a responsive frontend interface for a simple web application, following DecodeLabs' Project 1 guidelines:
- Use HTML, CSS, and basic JavaScript
- Build a responsive layout for different screen sizes
- Design a clean and user-friendly UI
- Apply mobile-first, semantic, and accessible development practices

---

## ✨ Features
- **Responsive Navigation** with a mobile sidebar menu and dropdown
- **Hero/Home Section** with call-to-action buttons
- **About Section** with feature highlights and animated counters
- **Dynamic Menu Tabs** (Starters, Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner) switchable via JavaScript
- **Testimonials Slider** showcasing customer reviews
- **Events Carousel** built with Swiper.js
- **Meet the Chefs** section with team member cards
- **Table Booking Form** with date, time, and guest count fields
- **Contact Section** with embedded Google Map and contact form
- **Footer** with address, contact info, and social links
- Scroll animations powered by **AOS (Animate On Scroll)**
- Icons via **Font Awesome**

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
| Technology | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| **HTML5** | Semantic page structure |
| **CSS3** | Styling, responsive layout (Grid & Flexbox) |
| **JavaScript** | Menu tab switching, sidebar toggle, counters, interactivity |
| **AOS.js** | Scroll-based animations |
| **Swiper.js** | Events carousel/slider |
| **Font Awesome** | Icons |
| **Google Fonts** | Typography (Amatic SC) |

